1. simple example
   $ scala p31.scala 200

2. above compiles each time called and will not output the compiled files in the
   current directory
   we can use scalac or fsc to compile
   $ scalac p31.scala
   $ fsc p31.scala

   then use scala or java to run a compiled file
   $ scala P31 200
   $ java -cp /home/d_a677356/downloads/scala/scala-2.12.6/lib/*:. P31 200

3. if a program import another class/object, we compile it this way:
   $ fsc ../utils/EulerUtils.scala P32.scala

   this will create all the .class files
   then we can run it either use scala or java same as above